  "sections": {
    "Description": "Alpha Spiders have very limited movement, but have the unique ability of throwing aSpiderling Eggon any column or row they are aligned with. This egg traps all surrounding entities in webs upon landing and will hatch into aSpiderlingon the next turn. The Spiderling's stats from the Alpha Spider are identical to that of the regularSpiders.\nAs a rare Vek, Alpha Spiders cannot spawn on the first island are are limited to one spawn per mission.",
    "Strategy": "With 4HP, Alpha Spiders are sturdier than regularSpidersand require more damage to take out. Still, dealing them is similar to the regular Spider; try to deploy your Mechs so that at most only one of them is webbed, then take out or wear down the Alpha Spider with ranged weapons, or wide area targeting weapons that can damage both the sticky egg and the Alpha Spider. If you cannot take it out in one strong hit, look to push it so that it falls on water or blocks an enemyspawn point."
  },
  "full_text": "Alpha Spider\nDetails\nHealth\n4\nMove\n2\nSystems\nLarge Offspring\n(\nEnemy\n)\nEffect\nThrow a sticky egg that hatches into a\nSpiderling\n.\nAlpha Spider\nis one of the Alpha\nVek\nfrom\nInto The Breach\n.\nDescription\n[\n]\nAlpha Spiders have very limited movement, but have the unique ability of throwing a\nSpiderling Egg\non any column or row they are aligned with. This egg traps all surrounding entities in webs upon landing and will hatch into a\nSpiderling\non the next turn. The Spiderling's stats from the Alpha Spider are identical to that of the regular\nSpiders\n.\nAs a rare Vek, Alpha Spiders cannot spawn on the first island are are limited to one spawn per mission.\nStrategy\n[\n]\nWith 4HP, Alpha Spiders are sturdier than regular\nSpiders\nand require more damage to take out. Still, dealing them is similar to the regular Spider; try to deploy your Mechs so that at most only one of them is webbed, then take out or wear down the Alpha Spider with ranged weapons, or wide area targeting weapons that can damage both the sticky egg and the Alpha Spider. If you cannot take it out in one strong hit, look to push it so that it falls on water or blocks an enemy\nspawn point\n.\nv\n·\nd\n·\ne\nVek\nVek\nBeetle\n•\nBlobber\n•\nBurrower\n•\nCentipede\n•\nCrab\n•\nDigger\n•\nFirefly\n•\nHornet\n•\nLeaper\n•\nScarab\n•\nScorpion\n•\nSpider\n•\nVolatile Vek\nVek (Advanced Edition)\nBouncer\n•\nGastropod\n•\nMosquito\n•\nMoth\n•\nPlasmodia\n•\nStarfish\n•\nTumblebug\nAlpha Vek\nAlpha Beetle\n•\nAlpha Blobber\n•\nAlpha Burrower\n•\nAlpha Centipede\n•\nAlpha Crab\n•\nAlpha Digger\n•\nAlpha Firefly\n•\nAlpha Hornet\n•\nAlpha Leaper\n•\nAlpha Scarab\n•\nAlpha Scorpion\n•\nAlpha Spider\nAlpha Vek (Advanced Edition)\nAlpha Bouncer\n•\nAlpha Gastropod\n•\nAlpha Mosquito\n•\nAlpha Moth\n•\nAlpha Plasmodia\n•\nAlpha Starfish\n•\nAlpha Tumblebug\nVek Psions\nBlast Psion\n•\nBlood Psion\n•\nShell Psion\n•\nSoldier Psion\nVek Psions (Advanced Edition)\nArachnid Psion\n•\nRaging Psion\n•\nSmoldering Psion\nVek Minions\nBlob\n•\nAlpha Blob\n•\nSpiderling Egg\n•\nSpiderling\n•\nAlpha Spiderling\nVek Minions (Advanced Edition)\nSpore\n•\nAlpha Spore\n•\nVicious Spore\n•\nBlob Leader\nVek Leaders\nBeetle Leader\n•\nFirefly Leader\n•\nHornet Leader\n•\nLarge Goo\n(\nMedium Goo\n) (\nSmall Goo\n) •\nPsion Abomination\n•\nScorpion Leader\n•\nSpider Leader\nVek Leaders (Advanced Edition)\nBlobber Leader\n•\nBouncer Leader\n•\nCentipede Leader\n•\nCrab Leader\n•\nGastropod Leader\n•\nMosquito Leader\n•\nPlasmodia Leader\n•\nScarab Leader\n•\nStarfish Leader\n•\nTumblebug Leader"
